node.title: Cool Pool
node.description: Another from Mize last weekend.  Glad I wore waders on this trip.  That water was freezing!

node.title: Mize Mill Under Cover
node.description: What a great weekend shooting waterfalls with a new friend, Todd, from the Alabama Shutterbugs.  Winter is a great time to get out to Bankhead and the Sipsey Wilderness after a rain.

node.title: Christmas Falls
node.description: The past few years around Christmas we've had significant rain fall, and for me it's the start of waterfall season in Alabama.  This is one of High Falls in the Talladega National Forest shot just before Christmas.

node.title: A bear out there
node.description: One of many black bears seen on our way to Jasper this summer.

node.title: A bright and shiny morning
node.description: This is pretty similar to a comp I posted of the Bon Secour Refuge a few weeks back, but there is a sunstar and some lens flare.  Not sure what I think of it.  Thoughts?
